description:
For the release of his ﬁrst EP, "The I", Indiscreet is pulling
out all the stops and delivering us witha universe of true beauty, in which we
ﬁnd ourselves immersed from the very ﬁrst listen.
Resembling French Touch, Indiscreet has already aroused much excitement
through his numerous remixes and explosive live performances in places
such as Lyon, Paris or Madrid. He has also already been scheduled to play
alongside diﬀerent artists as varied as the likes of Nathan Fake, Missil, MTGD,
Djedjotronic, Data, Costello, Digikid84 and even the renounced Cosmo Vitelli.
And if you have never had the opportunity to experience a music so
powerful that, as it blares through the speakers, the sheer force of it
blows all the cobwebs away, Indiscreet oﬀers the possibility thanks to his
corrosive basslines and a kick so distinct and unique that as soon as the switch
is triggered, the very depths of your innards vibrate with the beat.
The harmony of the melodies that burst through creates a dream-like
stampede that comes to an ﬁnish only at the end of the album...
In short, Indiscreet presents us with a jem of an album for anyone who values
good musical composition.

Tara Tinsley is a Singer/Songwriter who has been compared to artists like Miranda Lambert, Carrie Underwood, and Blondie all the while maintaining a fresh, unique sound which can definitely be heard in her release, "Meet Me Halfway". The EP features 7 rockin' songs including one she wrote with country star, Tracy Lawrence, called "More Sinners Than Saints".

Since that EP, she has released singles like "Better Early Than Never", a song dedicated to her niece who was born a micro preemie at 1 pound 2 ounces. "Like Your Daddy Does" is the song she wrote for her friend's father daughter dance and ended up using it for her own wedding as well. Her newest single,  "Get Back To Me", encompasses a Tom Petty Americana vibe that is a great jam to just chill out to or to listen to on those long drives.

Originally from Michigan, she moved to California in 2002 to pursue music, acting, and modeling. After spending many successful years in the sunny, beautiful state, she decided to dive deeper into her music and songwriting career by moving to Nashville in 2012. Now residing in Texas, she enjoys the country music scene and writes for TV/Film.

Over the course of her career she has performed at numerous major venues such as the MGM Grand Garden Arena in Las Vegas, Nevada, the Pontiac Silverdome in Michigan, California and the Angels Stadium in Anaheim, California. She has completed 3 tours of Japan and has opened for acts such as Smashmouth, Sister Hazel, Augustana, David Benoit, and Boston, demonstrating her musical diversity.

Continually touring the United States and writing songs every day like "Cheyenne's Eyes", the theme song for the TV show Cheyenne's Eyes, or  her newest single, "Get Back To Me," available on all digital platforms, she's one to watch in the music world.

Eduardo Castillo’s music encompasses his depth in the study of the industry and influences stemming from a South American and European upbringing. His studies in music compositions, orchestration and opera provide him with a vast understanding of harmonies, dynamics, and musical textures. Eduardo uses a subtle ethnomusicologist’s approach to music. His record collection reads like a music history book. In fact, his eclecticism is quite enticing. Sounds of Jazz, Avant-Garde, Middle Eastern, South American, Afro-Cuban folk, Soul, Funk, and Electronic Minimalism, can be heard in his compositions, his singing, his dj sets, and his playing of instruments, whether in their pure from or intertwined with down, mid and up-tempo electronic treatments. Ultimately, simplicity is what Eduardo strives for. An effort is always made to have fresh, organic sound while inevitably providing touches of technological advances shaping music today, never overwhelming and always sophisticated and tasteful.

Eduardo's mission is to always become a storyteller from beginning to end. Every record he plays has a very important intention. The music in his selections does not just fill time, it weaves in and out with dynamic and texture. The music and his improvisational live shows are brush strokes on a canvas that once he's reached the end, will look like a world of realism and fantasy all in one. He's a master at layering the musical with the technical and the surreal with the real.

Eduardo always leaves an indelible mark with his style and impeccable understanding of his environment.

Turntable addiction came at the conservatory where he studied classical music. In 2007 after returning from London with a huge collection of exclusive vinyl Roma Bromich opens itself to the public as a disc jockey. In 2008 moved to St. Petersburg where he organizes a series of successful conceptual parties every time bringing a wide range of quality electronic dj's. From the beginning of his musical career Roma Bromich play in the most interesting clubs in Saint-Petersburg and different cities in Russia and Europe. 
In St. Petersburg he does live shows with electronic music such as "In Between", "The Great Black", makes music for fashion show and theater performances.
Since 2018 lives in Moscow.

Flexi-musik

The flexi disc (also known as a phonosheet or Soundsheet, a trademark) is a phonograph record made of a thin, flexible vinyl sheet with a molded-in spiral stylus groove, and is designed to be playable on a normal phonograph turntable. Flexible records were commercially introduced as the Eva-tone Soundsheet in 1962, but were previously available in the Soviet Union as "rentgenizdat", "bones" or "ribs", underground samizdat recordings on x-ray film.
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flexi_disc

Sound designer, remixer, DJ & Producer in constant evolution, is always looking for new targets and more challenges, experimenting with uncommon paths and inventing innovative languages.
Hermanez has a unique style that transmits passion and adrenaline, dreams and emotions.
His genre evolved within the years and last years went back to more melodic music and organic house.
In 15 years of his professional career, he has created very much trademark sound: his tracks are perfectly weighted and well swung.
He creates his tension and dialogue between tracks that bring something new every time.
Michael is perhaps mostly associated with his grooving, and tribal-flecked tech house productions, which keep finding favor with the great and good including John Digweed, Hernan Cattaneo, Guy J, Lee Burridge.
2020 has added several successful works to Michael's discography that deserve special attention.
In April, Hermanez & Eran Aviner team up for the creative synergy and create something new and amazing.
Edge supply a three-track Progressive House masterpiece of an EP titled Aria.
The remix of the track "Koue" by Christian Lepah and Alin Dragan on the label "Double Trouble", which takes a step up with his signature atmospheric touch and intricate percussion.
The great remix of the track "Ours" by LØC on the label Akbal Music.
He brings the original track to another level.
In October, Souksonic welcomes Hermanez to the label with four original beauties, starting slow with the amazing "Cadell" track, then moving us with all the emotions and driving grooves he brings us "Driving thru India" and "Heavens of seven", and just check out the Bass on "Sweet Karma".
In March 2021, Peace Symphonies presents a remix by the Russian duo Volen Sentir on the track ‘Jinx’ by Hermanez & Lost Desert.
The remix immediately goes to first place in the Beatport Top 100 Organic House.
Hermanez constantly finds support from top labels and is published on All Day I Dream, Lost & Found, Shanti Radio Moscow, TrybesOf, Akbal, Magician on a duty, Hoomidaas, Souksonic, Edge, Sag & Tre.
Many large venues around the world are happy to see him at their events, he was a guest in Cafe D’anvers and Vaag (Belgium), Womb (Tokyo), Thuishaven Lost&Found (Amsterdam), Es Vedra (Buenos Aires), Deep in the palace (Romania), Bessonizza (Moscow).
His passion for creating a new sound and finding non-standard solutions grew into which evolved into mastering and mixing, helping artists with sound production.
All this transforms into creating sound packs which will be released on his Patreon page.
Hermanez working on studio content for other producers with sample packs and presets for certain software and hardware synthesizers.
One of the areas he is currently working on is creating a Live performance for All Day I Dream.
Hermanez is set to continue as one of the genre's most exciting talents in the next 12 months.
He remains focused, ambitious, and humble on his journey through music, and looks to prove why he’s a name to watch as the next generation of electronic artists.

DJ Ren was introduced to drum & bass around 1995-96, thrilled by the novelty and dynamism of the genre, felt she has finally found the music she was looking for. Found herself at the first d&b parties in the country and has been attending various gigs for years, listening to music, watching carefully every moves of the DJ’s. She has been waiting impatiently for the newest productions coming from overseas broadening her musical horizon. Around 1999 she got her first record which was Omni Trio’s remarkable album Byte Size Life in limited edition box set.

Early in the year 2001 borrowing decks and records she was trying to achieve what she was thinking of DJing by that time - soon she became obsessed with vinyls. Following a few gigs in smaller clubs in winter 2001 she was invited to the Nowsound promoted Ladies Night where she proved alongside Spice, Dazee and Jo Jo Rock that gentle sex is worthy of being part of the DJ comminity. In the following years she has been concentrating on her studies, meanwhile buying records and going to parties steadily, living together closely with the scene.

In 2004 she decided to start her radio show entitled Ren Radio Session on Torespont to present her ever-growing record collection including its not necessarily dancefloor-orientated pieces. Besides the prominent DJs of the local scene she hosted international guests like 0=0, Young Ax or Clever. With her arrival the team of the radio has got into its stride. Their work gained more recognition and became the no.1 only electronic music netradio in Hungary - which musical palette is ever broadening.

In the last years she got invites more often to play at Tilos Radio, the best-known Hungarian independent community FM radio, till last year she got her own weekly radioshow called Dzsungel Könyve (The Jungle Book) alongside DJ Cadik.
In the last 4-5 years due to the possibilities of the Internet Reni has been spotted by promoters home and abroad aswell, has gigs around Europe, in Austria, Germany, Romania, Serbia, Slovakia, etc. In her country she is frequently in the line-up's of the most significant promoters, such us Bladerunnaz, Drum Club, Braindeath, Jungle Ball and IPC events. Also loves to play on the countryside, often coming back to Debrecen, Szeged, Kecskemét, Pécs, Eger, Baja and Gyöngyös. She played alongside DJ Storm, DJ Flight, Alley Cat, Logistics, Cyantific, Rohan, Fierce, Equinox, 0=0, Martyn, Dj Lee, Survival and many more. She was also asked to record exclusive studio mixes, so her sets can be found at the biggest hungarian drum & bass site Impulsecreator and on various promoter websites. In her freetime she uses every effort to contribute to the scene, to give it more publicity, writing for Impulsecreator and Freee magazine, and urging new talents, showcasing their tunes in her shows.

Ren's musical taste is wide-ranging, from the more broken, experimenting dnb to dancefloor orientated music wherewith she drives people crazy - she finds her taste in both. Her all-time favourites are Photek, Source Direct and Ed Rush & Optical, and from the beginning to the present days she keeps her eyes especially on the releases of Paradox, Dillinja, Marcus Intalex, Total Science (Q-Project), Calibre, Digital & Spirit, Jonny L, Loxy&Ink and Keaton. On her gigs besides the aforementioned names she prefers liquid funk, ie. Hospital and Soul:R releases, however when she's on the air she frequently plays tunes from Paradox, Fracture & Neptune, 0=0, Polska, Macc, Dj Trax, Seba, Equinox, Breakage, Fanu and ICR. Her repertoire has been lately widen with promising "new" artists like Instra:mental, Icicle, Proxima, Data, Mutt, Redeyes, Deep Inc, Martsman, NSF Crew, Theory, Bop & Dephecta, Cycom, Con.struct, Selector Moldy, Insight and so on.

Skynet... its all in the name. Were somewhat the originators using the name for house music since 1994. Others who now use the name just consider us just another alias.
 
We have commercially sold over 5 million units of our music & productions since 1994 and are currently recording new material -Due later this year.

This profile is currently private & used to archive & share our entire recording sessions, stems, projects released and ditched raw and unreleased tracks from the past 21 years. 

In the meanwhile if you wish to follow our catalog please get intouch.

Ian Widgery makes a welcome debut on 852 under his Skynet UK moniker, having a career spanning over a decade (20 Years in 2010) with production credits for the likes of David Bowie, Human League, Robbie Williams and Faithless to name just a few. 
    
    SKYNET UK - BACK TO '89 - #1 DJ MAGAZINE CHART & #38 BEATPORT CHART 
        
     "Back To 89" takes us back to the old skool and harks back to days of the legendary Fantasia, Raindance and Exodus raves - a happy high energy piano driven monster, with a fierce bassline ripping through the track and awesome vocal samples that take the track to another level.
        
     Alex Calver (Twocker) delivers a stunning remix under his Calvertron guise - adding his trademark tough beats and tech house / electro stylings.
     An absolute essential in your set!
        
        DJ support already...
        
        DJ Stella Nutella (GO Magazine NL) - "2 awesome tracks that made me jump around with joy the first time I heard them, old school yet modern, both fit well in my set and are sure to rock the dance-floor at any time. Essential is the word! Really happy to discover this kick-ass producer and already hungry for more."
        
        Anna Kiss (DiFM) - "ABSOLUTE QUALITY!! I love it - i actually prefer the original, which suprised me! i thought i'd prefer the Calvertron mix, because I love his & twocker's stuff. on paper it sounds perfect - him doing a remix of an 89 inspired track, with his breaky filthy sounds - and it truly is.. I just feel it might terrify my audience in a club! I will definately be spinning his mix more on radio, i know that will go down extremely well on di.fm. I anticipate i'll be playing the original out more in clubs, i love all the old skool sounds. This package is right up my street, thank you. It will definately get a battering from me next week in Ibiza!"
        
        Robbie Lowe (Australia) - "Back To 89 - Original .... Absolutely massive ! Rave on !"
        
        Mark Holmes (Holmtik) - "Original is off the hook... Calvertron takes it back to the style of 'Double 99 - Ripgroove' in the days of 1997... woop woop! Massive remix! A surefire hit!"
        
        Filthy Rich - "Interesting track here :) Some nice ideas....the Calvertron mix is cool for my sets! Will give it a road test for sure... slave to the rave!"

Electronic, Dubstep, Drum and Bass Producer, DJ, and self-taught sound designer bringing a troublesome calamity of beats and sounds. Based in the gritty grimy underground. 

Including steady smooth cryptic beats encompass me and in my everyday life. Frequencies lead my pathway through doors of indestructible silence. There was peace before the bomb dropped.

Man and woman stand hand in hand together showing only signs of empowerment although the aftershock reveals torn faces and liberated spirits. 
Frozen solid in a mindless blog of atoms and neuron receptors we gather here to pay tribute to the waveforms that control our every move.
 We all tether in tandem rhythms and bass lines so surreal their artifacts are timeless in there own extent. 

Briskly carried on noticing the crowds move in unison with each passive sub melodic transfer. Can't be in it to win it because it is like a second love. You could pay me or just listen and my music will be produced just the same. As the working mechanics are sharpened to a razors point the invitation is clear and its arrival is eminent.

Always down to collaborate and share information and techniques with other artist and music producers so hit me up.

Myles Serg? is a DJ, musician and recording artist who has released on a vast swathe of labels including FEROX, Caduceus Records, Knotweed Records, Ilian Tape, Sweatshop, Night Drive Music, Metamorphic, Thema, Pushmaster Disc, and his own imprints (MS), RE(FORM), Space, (MS), and Dosed Recordings. He describes himself as a ?Reclusive Perfectionist?, whose haunting production sound reflects influences from early Detroit / Chicago electronic music. Myles has a style of his own that blurs the lines between techno and house. With his first introduction to techno back in the late 80?s he continued to nurturer his love for electronic music by DJing and producing. In 2001 he started his first imprint Dosed Recordings, which had a three-year run and featured the works of Mark Verbos, Kikoman, and Peter Sliwinski (Echoplex).

After a brief hiatus from music in 2005 Myles returned along with long time friend Brian Miller aka PHREK aka Detroit People Mover to create 6ONE6, A West Michigan based label that serves as platform for the catalog, release, and promotion of electronic music. 6ONE6 not only released music from both Myles and Brian it was also home to such artist as PLURAL aka James Johnson, Quantec, M. Rahn, Mike Dehnert, and Tommy Vicari Jnr. The label also became a platform for numerous musical projects including 1138 Music Inspired By The Film, Dreams of Home, and the 2011 V/A Flash, which involved the late Aaron Carl. Later that year Myles created his second imprint RE(FORM). RE(FORM) was Myles?s outlet to showcase his own productions; it also featured original productions from Myk Derill, Kazuya Kawakami, Ozka, and Sev Dah.

Myles also brought onboard friends such as Miles Sagnia, Jeroen Search, Abstract Division, Luis Ruiz, and Developer for remixes. Shortly after in 2011 Myles was invited to play Freerotation in Wales, UK which he is a full time resident since 2012. In later years Myles re-launched Dosed Recordings and created two additional imprints, SPACE and (MS). Currently Myles plays across the globe bringing his unique brand of techno to the masses. He has also teamed up with long time friend and mentor Donnell Knox to create S?ure Music Distribution, which was created to showcase labels and artist who push and expand the boundaries of creativity and innovation in sound.

description:
Born in 1969, Hervé has always been raised in a musical environment. 
  He started as a self-teached guitarist when he was 15 and played for various metal/punk bands including swiss cult noise act "Fear of God". 
  He got in touch with electronic music with his first computer in 1986 and started to produce songs with "Trackers" on Amiga. Quickly techno was a kind of "natural evolution" of his musical taste and he began a dj carrier using "Terrorist" as nickname which was the one he used when he was into computerhacking scene in 1988. 
  His mixing skill helped him to win the Mad club dj competition in 1994 (Laurent Garnier was a member of the jury) and the Swiss Producer & Dj competition in 1995. Meanwhile he started organizing techno events with "Androids", his own promotion team launched with a friend in 1993.
  In 1995 he became a member of Swiss biggest rave organisation "Raveland" and resident dj for swiss #1 electronic radio "Couleur 3" with a weekly show. At the same period he also joined French biggest techno booking agency "Tekmics" together with Miss Kittin, The Hacker, Miloch etc.. 
  1996 : with Raveland he owned the famous "Gallery of Sound" club in Geneva with guests like Jeff Mills, Acid Kirk, Manu Le Malin, Miss Djax, Lenny Dee, Eric Borgo etc.. and continued to launch large 20'000+ raves like "Pyramid" or "Family Tribe" (after the Street Parade 96). 
  In 1998 he started his own record label"Global Recordings" and launched two duo live-Pa concepts : "Ralph & Terrorist" (with Dj Ralph) and "Pyra All Stars" (with Dj Gemini), playing all over France and Switzerland.
  2002 : Terrorist is the first Swiss dj to select FinalScratch from Stanton for his future dj sets, he is now able to play more personal and self-edited stuffs.

For Sebastian Koch it all started in 1996, where he begann to spin Hip Hop records. In 1998 he visited the Tresor club for the first time and was so fascinated by the atmosphere, that his style changed completely. One year later he was playing for the first time at the legendary „HEADQUARTER-NEW FACES“ Nights at the Tresor club. In the year 2005 Sebastian adopted the Berlin studio of the Internet Radio "SPIEL-TRIEB" (www.spiel-trieb.org), which has its headquarter in Munich and works together with the well known club "HARRY-KLEIN". In 2007, together with 2 colleagues (0x7f & Subjunk), he founded the Label "31337-RECORDS". The Label is releasing international Artists such as "DEN", "SOMEONE-ELSE", "KAI" to name a few. On this Label he also released his first EP "FRIENDSHIP" along with "DEN". His style is straight minimal, sometimes dark, but always groovy Techno. True to the motto "less is more" or "the art lies in the detail"!
  
  ABOUT 31337 Records:
  
  The label was formed in early 2007 as a platform for international artists, to release quallity music for everyone over the internet. we have artists from all over the world, from underground to well known and respected producers such as someone else, remute, omar salgado, ditch, den, easy changes, kai, liiebermann, and many more.
  
  our focus lies mainly in minimal techno, dub and experimental electronic music. however, every artist can work freely and is not bound to any limitations in his style. because we all have more or less the same taste, but all in different directions, the result is a perfect mix between floor filling, subtle minimal techno, and deep, slow experimental tracks.
  
  the artist list keeps growing and 31337records presents their weekly shows on radio spiel-trieb (www.spiel-trieb.org) with lots of artists hosted by the label management. after one and a half years of work and 8 digital releases later, numerous requests for vinly releases resulted in the planning of the first 4 vinyl releases which are schedulled for the beginning of 2009. for the future, own events are planned around germany and possibly other countries in europe.
  
  as a label we will release 320bit mp3s, which will be made available for download.
  
  contact: info@31337records.com

Andrea was born in Udine (NE Italy) in 1974. It was the piano studies and the love for music that took him to start the DJ carreer at the early age of 16.

While his technique and taste grew, he worked in most of the clubs around the area. While gigging he also worked for some radio stations giving him the opportunity to learn about the music business. He was then was offered a job as pop/dance promoter for an independent promotion company, so he moved to Milan in 2000.

After 4 months he was spotted by the majors and hired by Universal Music Italia, where he signed Italian hit acts such as Sally Can Dance, DeNiro and Elgar. While there he also played a big role on the worldwide success of hits such as Modjo "Lady", Safri Duo "Played-a-live" and some more...

In 2001 he decided to leave Universal for Warner Music Italy, where he took the position of A&R Manager, head of the dance division. There he built up the three labels of the group: M.O.D.A. - Music Fashion (the house label), Antirecords (techno) and Y records (pop-dance label).

While working for Warner he signed hits from artists such as

    * DB Boulevard
    * Moony
    * Room 5
    * Tommy Vee
    * Gianni Coletti 

Meanwhile his DJ career was developing and he started to spin the records as a regular guest at the Old Fashion Cafe, the most glamourous club in Milan. During his stay at Warner Music he brought to success hits by acts such as

    * Craig David
    * Sean Paul
    * Missy Elliott
    * Talking Heads
    * Jarabe De Palo
    * Cesare Cremonini
    * Kevin Lyttle
    * Dannii Minogue
    * Holly Valance
    * Live Elements
    * Robbie Rivera
    * Ruffneck
    * Inaya Day
    * Narcotic Thrust
    * The Streets
    * Chicane
    * Kings of Tomorrow
    * Brandy
    * Dirotta su Cuba
    * Raf

...and many more.

Between 2003 and 2004 he's also been consulting for Warner Chappell Music Italiana.

Finally in 2004 he left Warner to build up his own record company, and took with him all the brands of the labels he had established while there, plus added a couple more: FullFX (black music), Oldies! (Catalogue), and WhitePlus (avantgarde label). During the past years the hightlights of the labels group have been:

    * Nicola Fasano
    * Gianni Coletti
    * Dr.Alban
    * Vasco Rossi

mau5trap artist Dom Kane is a name heard globally in DJ sets from the likes of Dave Seaman, Deadmau5, Orbital, and James Zabiela to name a few, with international radio plays on BBC Radio 1 & Sirius (Pete Tong), Capital FM (Andi Durrant), and Apple Beats 1 (Deadmau5). Dom has engineered for several UK Top 40 artists recording vocals and instrumentation including Sian Evans (Kosheen), Chris Jones (Armada), and more. As a DJ, Dom has held residencies at some of the worlds most legendary clubs including Space Ibiza and Ministry Of Sound in London.

As a sound designer, the name Dom Kane has appeared in factory presets for synthesisers including FXpansion (D-CAM & Geist), Xfer (Nerve/Serum), Ohm Force (Ohmicide), Cakewalk (Rapture Pro), and the legendary hardware synth company Moog (Animoog, Little Phatty, Slim Phatty, Sub 37 Tribute). Since Dom Kane was featured with an Artist Series sample pack on Loopmasters back in 2008, his sound banks and samples have appeared in studios worldwide via his own label Quantum Loops too.

The past few years alone saw Dom Kane ascending fast amongst the ranks of House music producers: his singles and remixes topping the online Top 40 (Signal Rejected, Space, Blagger); as well as having a full artist feature and front cover DVD in Future Music Magazine, and Computer Music Magazine. Ministry Of Sound TV have released several worldwide exclusive previews of his work across their networks, gaining over 20,000 plays in in the space of hours on the MOS YouTube channel, and his music was featured in the League Of Legends global gaming competition with millions of plays to just his tracks alone.

BIOGRAPHY

Dimitri has been passionate about music from a very early age. 
His first releases date from more than 10 years ago and got played by big names like Carl Cox, Mark Broom, Luke Slater and many others. Since then, Dimitri evolved and built up his carreer as an experienced high quality dj and producer.

In 2003 came a first break-through when he released 'Panther ep' on the prestigious and artistically highly appreciated label Music Man. The ep sold well, received many positive reviews and delivered invitations to perform at major European parties like I Love Techno.

More releases followed and Dimitri continued working and producing in his studio on lots of different projects, always with lots of attention to the groove in his work. His productions are getting played worldwide by the biggest dj's who all appreciate this typical groove and the pro-pulsing arrangements as ideal ingredients to make the floor go wild.

In 2008, Dimitri released a new pearl, 'Run and hide'. The track was a first step in a more emotional direction of his productions. Soon after he made remixes for Marc Romboy and Chelonis R jones (Get Physical) on Systematic recording. As well as some very deep emotional remixes he also made more energetic remixes on MBelektronics, Girafe sauvage that Year.

More collaborations with other DJ's, artists and producers take place again in 2009. Dimitri has been working with Marc Romboy in the studio and together they remixed a track from Marc's latest Album, 'The Beat'. A few months after Dimitri released 'Pharaoh'. He produced not only the music, but also a video on this track. As he's also working on tv commercials and on different side-projects, these experiences reflect more and more in his cinematic way of arranging tracks. Due to these experiences, Dimitri now creates a musicvideo on most of his releases. As he finds this a much better and visual way to communicate with his fans. This exceptional visual aspect is very important for Dimitri. It will definitely be something he will work on even more in the future.

ANNA is one of Brazil’s finest exports and she’s quickly climbing the ranks with her seductive yet heavy-hitting brand of techno
― Mixmag

The world might have stopped during the pandemic, but ANNA never rested. The globally renowned techno DJ used the downtime to further her sound and craft a wave of new music. Since she secured a summer hit with 2019's 'Forever Ravers' with Kittin, she has explored immersive ambient next to powerful techno on a range of vital labels from Drumcodfe to Plus 8, Mute Records to Ahead of Our Time. As her streaming numbers continued to soar, ANNA eventually got back to the DJ booth and lit up dance floors around the globe.
Since November 2020, ANNA has shared her vast production skills with the world via The Anaweh Studio Masterclass. They offer over 10 hours of in-depth content and techniques alongside her countryman Wehbba and more than 1500 students to date have benefitted. They are crafted from the skills ANNA has picked up over more than 20 years in the dance music industry. In that time she has accomplished plenty including a BBC Essential Mix, featuring on the cover of DJ Mag North America, playing a live-streamed set for Cercle that has been viewed more than two million times and plenty more besides.  
On the production front recently, ANNA continues to reach new heights and evolve and enrich her sound with every new track. She has released her always powerful, driving sounds on essential labels like Drumcode, Novamute and Domino amongst many more. She is also an in demand remixer who has taken on classics such as ‘Belfast’ by Orbital, ‘Howler’ by Martin Gore's Depeche Mode, ‘Trilogy’ by Chris Liebing and Grimes's ‘So Heavy I Fell Through the Earth,’all of which show her diversity. Add in original singles such as ‘Another Dream’ on Ahead of Our Time, 'Overflow' on an Afterlife compilation, ‘High Contrast’ on the legendary Plus8 and an EP on Drumcode and you have an artist at the top of her game.
Today’s success has been two decades in the making, stretching back to the nightclub her father owned in the countryside outside São Paulo, where she honed her craft as a DJ from the age of 14. Her journey since then has been marked by passion, hard work and unrelenting dedication to her craft. You can see this when she plays – a skilled and accomplished selector, her performances are energetic, engaging and captivating. Gigs at the legendary Warung, D-Edge and Time Warp Brazil in her home country are the stuff of legends, while globally she’s in ever-increasing demand playing everywhere from Movement Detroit, Awakenings, Tomorrowland and DC10.

Creepy Finger Records boss Terry Whyte first became an established name on his local circuit over a decade ago. Having played everywhere from Sub Club to under Glasgow’s legendary Arches, his Creepy Finger nights carved out their own reputation in the city’s famous scene.  
After studying audio engineering and getting to know the Glasgow party scene like the back of his hand during his 20s, he has a deep understanding of sound technology as well as what makes a club full of techno fans tick.
This makes Terry equally comfortable whether behind the decks, locked away in his studio creating new tracks / remixes or knee-deep in audio mastering.
Establishing a memorable sound of his own seems to have come naturally to Terry. Rolling bass-driven grooves that’ll have your shoulder twitching form the spine of his journey-like sets, only taking his crowd to darker and more twisted places when they’re ready.
Partygoers around the globe are becoming well used to that trademark Creepy sound. As a prolific producer with support from the likes of Richie Hawtin, Green Velvet and Marco Carola, audiences at major festivals such as Burning Man, Awakenings, Timewarp and Sonar have been treated to his and his label’s productions.
Creepy Finger’s conveyor belt of grooves shows no sign of slowing down and Terry has also linked up with Carlo Ruetz’s (Moonplay) and Justin James’s (Refused) labels.
Having dedicated much of his time to establishing Creepy Finger Records as a force to be reckoned with, Terry’s gigs are now taking centre stage. Having played to crowds everywhere from Belgium to Hungary and Germany to Ibiza, South America and beyond, the coming months will see Terry Whyte reconnecting with his fan base all over the world.

MR. TOPHAT

Born in Sweden in 1990 this guy is a true Stockholm original. Having had more than two dozens of his own productions released it’s almost an understatement to say that Rudolf Nordström aka Mr. Tophat has a real passion for dance music. 
This has led him to start his well-reputed label Karlovak, co-run with Art Alfie since 2011. “House music for club nights that most certainly can’t end” is how the founders describe it, which gives you an idea of what we are talking about. 

Mr. Tophat is also in charge of his own imprint Junk Yard Connections founded in 2009, a label operated with the motto 'strictly limited, no repress' – by saying that it is not much of a surprise these records sell out fast. In terms of Tophat’s own productions he ended 2016 with outputs on labels Public Possession and Music for Freaks, and earlier in the year also working with fellow Swede pop star Robyn, remixing two singles, being part of her live band and together releasing the single “Trust Me EP“ for Norwegian label Smalltown Supersound. 

Mr. Tophat is an interesting contradictive artist to follow - audibly as well as visually. Nordström moves confidently and freely between sonic worlds, never compromising, instead continuously building and strengthening his own unique foundation in sound.

With his wide-open tone and wryly witty compositions, Colorado-based guitarist Vic Dillahay blends a myriad of styles into an unmistakably unique voice. For over 20 years, he has refined this distinctive sound with numerous jazz ensembles, Liam O'Beirne's progressive Celtic band Indigent Row, and the fusion trio Graphite Addiction with Pete Ehrmann (Generations) and Tim Carmichael (3ology). His discography is equally eclectic, having appeared on over 25 albums ranging from swing jazz to electronic noise. His recent solo work explores the rich history of American music with free-roving jazz, blues, and rock-tinged improvisations.

Vic is committed to supporting music education for everyone, teaching all ages and levels of experience at Boomer Music Company in Fort Collins and Guitars, Etc. in Longmont. He is a sought after clinician and coach across the region with an emphasis on jazz guitar at the middle and high school level. Some of his students have gone on to study music at Berklee School of Music, The University of North Texas, and The University of Colorado Denver and a number of them are currently professional musicians. He is a board member with the Longmont Jazz Association and is the chair of its education committee.

It was the year 1994. when me and my family moved from the places between cold Siberian forests and noble deserts of Uzbekistan to the land of Serbia. In the passing years I have started attending the music school (for a classical guitar and later, lute) which helped me develop my life style in the more artistic direction. However, I was never too keen to be the usual “player” of music and spend my life by using my musical knowledge to present some melodies and compositions that were created by other people years, decades or centuries ago. I wanted to have something of my own. So, I was polishing my style and searching inspirations by playing in various groups and ensembles. Being an admirer of a darker side of music I have participated in some projects and bands which covered my interests. One which is mostly worth of a mention is an acoustic black metal group Strevlosh Zvezda. As much as it was satisfying to participate in something with such unique attitude for music, the desire to explore my own musical ways remained. So in the year of 2005 I’ve decided to start giving shapes through music to the ideas I had all these years. My first plan was to play atmospheric black metal. For the name I chose Tamerlan after the ancient well known Uzbek war-leader and sorcerer. This was also a synonym for my own name. But after some time it was clear to me that black metal, and metal music itself was too limiting for everything I wanted to create. So, I let my music evolve into the mystical and dark ambient form. Here, I was free to experiment with sounds and atmosphere to make a perfect soundtrack to my visions of this world and far beyond it (for this world as it is today, is incredibly uninspiring place to live in). Finally, the 21st of March in the year 2006 was the day when the first Tamerlan demo was finished. It contained four instrumental compositions full of mystical, archaic and occult atmosphere. The strange thing about it was that this demo was released on the 670th birthday of the real Tamerlan. And this wasn’t done on purpose. For the music itself, it was in spite of low production quality very well accepted by audience and critics. I also got an opportunity to present my music live on the Samhain 2006 festival organized by Dark Revolution. For that opportunity I have gathered my friends to help me on stage. This also brought a deal between me and Dark Revolution label called Insurrection to release some of my works. First to be released was an EP called Full Moon Festival. This time, among other things, the production was on the level for this time I had full professional equipment to record on. It was released officially in the 3rd of June, year 2007 followed by the live promotion. In spite of my wish to leave Tamerlan as a one man project, I still continue to cooperate with my friends and colleagues for the occasional live performances. However, the biggest part still remains within the studio work, and it’s own affection upon everyone who listens to it.

Michael is a creative and ambitious music producer and sound designer from Scotland. He has travelled across the globe for many years, working in the music industry in the likes of Los Angeles, London and Berlin.
 
Michael has developed his sound and technique by taking huge influences from his ever changing surroundings. This has helped him mould together a distinctive sound. Whether it is his funky minimal extracts or the rolling late hour tech house, Michael embodies a sound that helps to intertwine with your body and mind, creating a true listening experience.
 
This talent has seen him release a number of hits on Slovakian minimal label Leporelo. With each track possessing bouncy catchy bass lines, slamming drums and a wide array of glitched out percussion and effects. These delightful little morsels soon tickled the taste buds of M-nus artist Ambivalent, which soon saw the him  chart  “Greasy Love” in his October Glass Half Full Chart.
 
And it wasn't too long till Michael attracted other top DJ’s. The likes of Richie Hawtin and Dubfire started to play a selection of Michael tracks across 2011 and 2012. This lead onto Richie using Michael’s track “Wa” his essential mix on Pete Tong Radio 1 show.
